The paper deals with a data structure for answering kth-nearest neighbor queries, which is a common problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of sublinear space is also a common theme in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of the data structure for proximity search, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
